{{Tool-stub}}

'''Eikon''' is a set of software products provided by [[Refinitiv]] for financial professionals to monitor and analyse financial information. It provides access to real time [[market data]], news, fundamental data, analytics, trading and messaging tools.

The main product runs on [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] and lets users compose customized views on multiple screens. It also extends [[Microsoft Office]] with data retrieval addins. Eikon subscribers can access Eikon data from their [[smartphones]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Eikon for Android|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.thomsonreuters.eikon|website=play.google.com|accessdate=2 February 2015}}</ref> [[iPad]], or from a web browser.<ref>{{cite news| title=December 12th: easier access via Eikon Web| url=http://alphanow.thomsonreuters.com/2014/12/december-12th-easier-access-via-eikon-web/}}</ref>

==History==
Thomson Reuters launched Eikon in 2010<ref>{{cite web|title=Thomson Reuters to launch next generation desktop|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/thomsonreuters-eikon-idUSN1016161520100913|website=Reuters}}</ref> as a replacement of [[Reuters 3000 Xtra]], Reuters’ earlier platform. In October 2018 Eikon was transferred to [[Refinitiv]] as a result of a larger deal between [[The Blackstone Group|Blackstone]] and the Financial & Risk business of [[Thomson Reuters]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Thomson Reuters closes deal with Blackstone, rebrands as Refinitiv |url=https://www.thetradenews.com/thomson-reuters-closes-deal-blackstone-rebrands-refinitiv|website=The TRADE}}</ref>.

==Pricing==
At the end of 2013, an Eikon subscription was reported to cost from $300 to $1,800 per month, the average setup being around $800 per month.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Nilsen|first1=Sverre Rørvik|url=http://blogs.cfainstitute.org/insideinvesting/2013/12/10/the-secret-revolution-in-finance/|website=blogs.cfainstitute.org/| title=The Secret Revolution in Finance|accessdate=2 February 2015}}</ref>

